1
00:00:00,208 --> 00:00:02,208
They interrogated me about three times

2
00:00:04,208 --> 00:00:08,208
Of course, every two or three days
they would come to interrogate me

3
00:00:08,291 --> 00:00:11,125
Then they would take me not
to this room, but to another one

4
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:17,333
For interrogation. There was no beating, not once
did they hit me, only question and answer each time

5
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:24,041
Interviewer: Did they propose that you work with them in exchange for your release?

6
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:31,041
Yes, they did propose that. They
proposed that I work with them

7
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:35,208
To bring them news about the Free
Syrian Army since I had relatives there

8
00:00:36,375 --> 00:00:41,333
I told them I had no contact with them.
I told them I had no contact with them

9
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:48,250
And I couldn’t go to those areas, things like that

10
00:00:48,625 --> 00:00:51,416
They went silent and never brought it up again

11
00:00:51,541 --> 00:00:59,166
Interviewer: Do you remember the names of the
interrogators? Surely they called each other by name?

12
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:02,875
How did they call each other? Do you remember the names?

13
00:01:03,208 --> 00:01:09,500
There was someone called Abu Abdullah,
Syrian, speaking in a Syrian dialect

14
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:18,416
Of course they were all masked, and there was another one they called Shaqran

15
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:23,291
These are the names I remember clearly

16
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,750
Interviewer: What was their dialect and from which country?

17
00:01:25,791 --> 00:01:30,125
Witness: Shaqran’s accent was Saudi, and Abu Abdullah’s was Syrian

18
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:36,875
Interviewer: During the interrogation, did they have
a lot of information about you or only simple details?

19
00:01:36,875 --> 00:01:39,791
Interviewer: How did he question you to get information from you?

20
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:47,291
During the interrogation they
already had some information about me

21
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:51,291
Meaning that before they detained me, they had asked about me

22
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:55,125
Interviewer: Did they threaten you, for example, with your family?

23
00:01:57,750 --> 00:02:02,208
Or that they would harm your family if you didn’t confess?

24
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:07,416
Of course, they never threatened me, neither
with my family nor with myself, nor anything

25
00:02:07,875 --> 00:02:11,291
There was no threat or beating during the interrogation

26
00:02:13,833 --> 00:02:17,166
Interviewer: Did the interrogation
involve psychological or physical torture?

27
00:02:18,250 --> 00:02:26,166
During the interrogation they didn’t torture me at all, didn’t hit me,
and didn’t insult me, just a normal question-and-answer interrogation

28
00:02:31,208 --> 00:02:37,791
Interviewer: During your time in prison, what were the
tools or methods they used to torture other prisoners?

29
00:02:38,375 --> 00:02:45,000
I saw here the <i>balingo</i> [hoist for suspension],
where they tie a person’s hands and lift him up

30
00:02:45,625 --> 00:02:53,000
That was one of the torture methods. There were many others, but I didn’t
see them, I only heard about them outside, I didn’t see anything myself

31
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:57,208
Interviewer: Was the torture applied
to all the prisoners or only specific people?

32
00:02:57,250 --> 00:03:04,541
To specific people, only specific ones were tortured,
depending on the charges brought against them

33
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:09,250
Interviewer: Did you hear that
there were women imprisoned here?

34
00:03:09,666 --> 00:03:13,333
I heard there were women prisoners
here, but I didn’t see any of them

35
00:03:13,625 --> 00:03:16,333
Interviewer: You didn’t even hear
the sound of women being tortured?

36
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:20,541
No, I didn’t hear women’s voices, and I didn’t see any women

37
00:03:21,041 --> 00:03:26,375
I didn’t see anyone at all. I used to hear
sounds, but they were men’s voices, not women’s

38
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:30,291
But I did hear that there were
women here, that they brought women

39
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:35,916
Interviewer: Did any prisoner die
here under torture during your time?

40
00:03:37,458 --> 00:03:45,458
During my time in prison I didn’t hear that anyone died

41
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:51,791
But there was a man I heard them say, We’ll execute
him, we’ll execute him, but I didn’t see anything

42
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:54,875
I wasn’t sure if they were just trying to scare him or not

43
00:03:56,875 --> 00:03:59,833
Interviewer: Can you recall the names
of any prisoners who were held with you?

44
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:04,958
Names of prisoners held with me... I don’t
remember at all, because I didn’t see anyone

45
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:10,541
All the time I spent here was in solitary confinement.
I saw one person, but I don’t know his name
